27/12/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Foreign Minister Besnik Mustafaj said on Monday (26 December) that Kosovo and its future status would be priority issues on Albania's foreign policy agenda in 2006.
Speaking to Radio Free Europe, Mustafaj cited progress in Euro-Atlantic integration, regional co-operation, and contributions to regional security as other priorities.
In other news, Albania's Supreme Court President Thimio Kondi called on the legislative and executive powers to boost efforts Friday in fighting corruption in the national judiciary.
Kondi is proposing the launch of an inter-department task force, which would draft tougher measures against corruption as well as examine individual cases of alleged corruption.
(Albanian News - 27/12/05)
